    <section>
        <div id="heading">ABOUT</div>
        <h3>What is Volunteer work?</h3>
        <p>Volunteer work refers activities individuals undertake on their own and offer their time, skills, and energy to help others or contribute to a cause without expecting financial compensation. It is typically organized by nonprofit organizations, charities, community groups, or governmental agencies to address various social, environmental, or humanitarian needs.</p><br><br>
        <h3>What we do?</h3>
        <p>This platform is a one stop destination for people passionate about giving back to the society by volunteering for social, environmental and humanitarian causes. We curate such opportunities according to your interests, making sure that you do not miss out on selfless activities! Your account here keeps record of your contributions and the impact of the cause you worked for.</p><br>
        <h3>How can you contribute?</h3>
        <p>Volunteer work can encompass a wide range of activities, including:
        <br><ul><li>
        Direct Service: This involves working directly with individuals or communities in need. Examples include serving meals at a soup kitchen, tutoring children, visiting elderly residents in nursing homes, or providing assistance to people with disabilities.</li><br> <li>   
        Advocacy and Awareness: Volunteers may engage in activities to raise awareness about important issues or advocate for social change. This can include organizing rallies or protests, lobbying policymakers, or running campaigns to promote awareness of specific causes.</li><br><li>       
        Fundraising and Development: Volunteers often help nonprofit organizations raise funds to support their programs and activities. This can involve organizing events such as charity auctions, marathons, or bake sales, as well as soliciting donations from individuals or businesses.</li><br><li>        
        Environmental Conservation: Many volunteer opportunities focus on protecting and preserving the environment. This may involve activities such as planting trees, cleaning up parks or beaches, monitoring wildlife populations, or promoting recycling and sustainability practices.</li><br> <li>           
        Disaster Relief and Emergency Response: Volunteers play a crucial role in responding to natural disasters, humanitarian crises, and other emergencies. They may provide immediate assistance such as distributing food and supplies, assisting with search and rescue efforts, or offering emotional support to affected individuals.</li><br></ul></p>
    </section>
